h every filter combination (kind, status, tag, type, target, assignee)\n14. Find returns empty slice, not nil\n15. List with sort by priority, created, updated\n16. List with limit\n17. Find after closing all notes — no results for default status filter\n\n### Error handling\n18. Append to non-existent note ID — should error\n19. Create with empty kind — what happens?\n20. Get with garbage ID — error, not panic\n21. Fold with ID that partially matches multiple notes\n22. Context on path with no notes — empty, not error\n\n### Data integrity\n23. Create a note, restart engine (NewEngine again on same repo), fold — data survives\n24. Create notes, Rebuild(), verify index matches\n25. Doctor on healthy repo — no broken edges\n26. Doctor on repo with deliberately broken edges (append referencing non-existent target)\n\n### Concurrent safety\n27. Parallel Creates from multiple goroutines — no data corruption\n28. Parallel Appends to same note — all events present after fold\n29. Parallel Find while Creates happening\n\n### CRDT/YDoc wiring (if testable)\n30. Create note with body, edit body, verify CRDT state updated\n31. Multiple body edits, fold — verify latest body wins and edit count correct\n\n## Build and run\n\n```bash\nnix-shell -p go --run 'go test ./test/ -count=1 -timeout 180s -run TestEngine -v'\n```\n\nAlso verify ALL existing tests still pass:\n```bash\nnix-shell -p go --run 'go test ./... -count=1 -timeout 180s'\n```\n\n## Rules\n- Every test must PASS. If you find a real bug, write the test to demonstrate the current behavior (not the ideal), and add a comment `// BUG: \u003cdescription\u003e` so we know.\n- Use `t.Run()` subtests for grouping.\n- Error messages must be diagnostic — include got/want values.\n- If a test needs setup that takes \u003e5s, use `testing.Short()` skip.\n- Commit when all tests pass.","assignee":"adversarial-engine","tags":["team"],"body":"You are a HOSTILE test engineer. Your mission: write the most brutal, adversarial test sui